    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Savannah, Ga.</placeName>
                <date>Feb. 18th 1867</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><sic>Inclosed</sic> please find check<lb/> for One Hundred &amp;
                Eight dollars, as per account<lb/> stated below. Of the four Bibles you sent me,
                one<lb/> is without clasps, &amp; therefore the cost of which is<lb/> fifteen
                Dollars, as you told me when you <sic>was</sic> here, the<lb/> bill says Twenty
                Dollars, I have kept it for myself<lb/> &amp; send you accordingly 15 Dollars for
                the same</p>
            <p><persName>Miss Mininis<add>?</add></persName> has not paid me, &amp; I am a bad
                hand<lb/> at collecting from the ladies. I collected from<lb/> cash from myself
                17.75</p>
            <table cols="2" rows="8">
                <row>
                    <cell>“ <persName>I. Cohen</persName></cell>
                    <cell>1—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Hess</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>20—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>S Gardner</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>20—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>L Stern</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>4.75</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Bergel</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>9—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Hertz</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>11—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Solomons</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">29 50</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Total</cell>
                    <cell>108.00</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p><persName>Mr Solomons</persName> 21 Dollars for the large Bible, &amp; 8.50 which<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Walter</persName> had against him<lb/> for you. The small Bible,
                he<lb/> says he will dispose of as<lb/> soon as possible &amp; remit<lb/> you the
                amt. I have on<lb/> hand subject to your order:<lb/> 3 Crucifixion &amp; 1
                Calendar<lb/> anything in my power, which I can do<lb/> to serve you I will do with
                pleasure</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Simon E Ryck</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
